    "discriminators": [
     "A real morphology, not just a name: acid burning and sizzling is a dense FIZZ - a very high onset rate of tiny unresolvable bubble-collapse events that fuse into a bright, near-stationary, low-crest HISS with almost no low-frequency energy. Sustained, noisy, HF-dominated. That is measurable, and it separates ACID from the discrete plops of CHEMICALS-REACTION: signal_narrowable.",
     "Against CHEMICALS-REACTION: onset_rate and centroid are the axis. ACID = dense, fine, bright, fused (fizz/sizzle). REACTION = sparse, coarse, low, resolvable (bubble plops, glugs). This is the same sparse-vs-dense split that separates DRIP from FIZZ generally.",
     "It does NOT separate acid from a frying pan (FOOD_DRINK), a fire hiss (FIRE), a steam leak (AIR-HISS) or carbonation - they are the same physics, and 'acid' is a story about the liquid, not a property of the sound. Text decides that.",
     "A melting/eating-through element adds a low bubbling layer that pulls low_band_energy up and blurs the boundary with REACTION."
    ],
