    "discriminators": [
     "Bubbling and foaming: a texture of RESOLVABLE discrete events. Each bubble collapse is a short, damped, pitched plop whose frequency falls as the bubble radius rises, so the material has a moderate onset_rate, a much lower centroid than a fizz, real mid/low-band content and a higher crest_factor (individual plops still stand above the bed). That sparse-and-coarse morphology is measurable, hence signal_narrowable.",
     "Against CHEMICALS-ACID: dense/bright/fused (ACID) vs sparse/low/resolvable (REACTION). If individual bubbles are countable, it is REACTION.",
     "The explanation itself concedes overlap with LIQUID & MUD, and that overlap is total on signal: a beaker bubbling and a mud pot bubbling are the same sound. A bunsen burner adds a stationary gas-flame hiss, which pulls the file toward FIRE/AIR. Text decides all of it.",
     "Confusable with boiling water and any underwater/aeration bed."
